{
  "doc_id": "33492",
  "text": "Monte Carlo generators are widely used tools in high energy physics since they provide an essential input helping to understand detector effects. In consequence, they provide a way of comparison between the theory and experimental data. Elastic scattering process is present in many recent HEP MC generators. Based on the formulas described in the previous section, the process of elastic scattering has been added to the GenEx MC generator [CITATION_1] .",
